explanation:
- OS_ObjectIdTransactionFinish: Direct callee of the target; its implementation must be inspected for any use of memcmp on null-terminated strings (and to understand how final_id is used/propagated).
- OS_ObjectIdGlobalFromToken: Called by OS_ObjectIdTransactionFinish (per the call graph); include to check for memcmp usage in lower-level object ID handling.
- OS_Lock_Global and OS_Unlock_Global: Called by OS_ObjectIdTransactionFinish; include for completeness in case they call into utilities that use memcmp on strings.
- OS_NotifyEvent: Direct callee of the target; its implementation must be checked for any memcmp use when handling the event and the token->obj_id parameter.
- OS_object_token_t (struct definition): Needed to know the type and semantic of token->obj_id (e.g., whether it is a string/pointer) to determine if memcmp could be (mis)used on a null-terminated string.
- osal_id_t (typedef): Needed to determine the underlying type of IDs (integer vs pointer/char*) so an occurrence of memcmp would or would not be comparing null-terminated strings.
- OS_SUCCESS (macro/enum) and OS_OBJECT_ID_UNDEFINED (macro/constant): Needed to fully understand control flow and the values assigned/used (helps track whether string semantics are involved).
- OS_EVENT_RESOURCE_DELETED (macro/constant): Included because it is passed into OS_NotifyEvent; the handling code might differ by event type and thus influence whether string comparisons occur.
- memcmp (standard library function): Include the symbol so the analyzer can detect any direct or indirect uses of memcmp in the listed functions (to determine if it is being used to compare null-terminated strings).
